Thunderstorms wreaked havoc across the middle Mississippi Valley

and the Southeast on Wednesday with lethal tornadoes, wind up to 100 mph and hail up to the size of baseballs.
One twister smashed into a residential district, a shopping area and a school, killing at least two people and causing dozens of injuries, police said.
Southern Illinois was also hard hit by the storms, with one woman killed by a falling tree, about 20 people injured and power lines downed.
Severe thunderstorms also developed over Alabama and South Carolina during the afternoon, and the weather service reported a tornado north of Greenwood, S.C.
